This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on May 21, 2012. The memorandum designates officers of the National Archives and Records Administration (NARA) to act as Archivist of the United States in the event that the Archivist or Deputy Archivist is unable to perform their duties. The designated officers, in order of succession, are the Chief Operating Officer, Executive for Agency Services, Director of the National Personnel Records Center, and Director of the George W. Bush Library. The memorandum also includes exceptions and limitations to this order of succession, and revokes a previous memorandum from 2006. It clarifies that the memorandum does not create any legally enforceable rights or benefits. The Archivist is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.